<title>USA: H.B. Fuller unit to raise adhesive prices.</title>
<headline>H.B. Fuller unit to raise adhesive prices.</headline>
<dateline>ST. PAUL, Minn. 1997-03-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>H.B. Fuller Co's North American adhesives unit said Wednesday it will raise prices four to six percent on its hot melt, water-based, and certain specialty adhesive product lines, effective April 30.</p>
<p>The company said the price rise was due to price increases on many of the fundamental raw materials used in the formulation of the products, as well as supply and demand imbalances that exist with certain basic petrochemical feedstocks.</p>
<p>H.B. Fuller fell 1-1/2 to 46-1/2 Wednesday.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk, 312-408-8787))</p>
